JOHANNESBURG - The father of a South Africa man held hostage in Mali is considering going to that country. Stephen McGown and Swedish national Johan Gustafsson were abducted by al-Qaeda in November 2011.Stephen s father, Malcolm, wants to push Mali s authorities to help with operations to release them.READ: In the hands of al Qaeda: McGown still aliveOver the weekend, Stephen s mother, Beverly, died without being reunited with her son.The family says her final wish was to see him again.Relief organisation Gift of the Givers has been trying to secure their release.eNCA